steps.description:
Visit the home improvement store to find plywood to create the bench seat and possibly a small shelf underneath. 1″x 2-1/4″ pieces may work well. You’ll need enough plywood to make two long rectangle boxes inside the bench (sizes will vary from the back of the two chairs to the desired bench length). If you plan to add a shelf, you will also need pieces of wood to make the slats. Purchase a flat piece of plywood that will become the actual bench. Measure the width and length to arrive at the right size. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/6a/Make-a-French-Bench-from-Two-Chairs-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-French-Bench-from-Two-Chairs-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/6/6a/Make-a-French-Bench-from-Two-Chairs-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/aid3045272-v4-728px-Make-a-French-Bench-from-Two-Chairs-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"485","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Pick up several 3” screws (at least seven) that will be used to pull the bench together. Don’t forget to purchase or find your electric drill to make the process go quickly. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/23/Make-a-French-Bench-from-Two-Chairs-Step-2Bullet4.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-French-Bench-from-Two-Chairs-Step-2Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/2/23/Make-a-French-Bench-from-Two-Chairs-Step-2Bullet4.jpg/aid3045272-v4-728px-Make-a-French-Bench-from-Two-Chairs-Step-2Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"485","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Using pieces of the chair you disassemble, nail them together forming a rectangle. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/35/Make-a-French-Bench-from-Two-Chairs-Step-6Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-French-Bench-from-Two-Chairs-Step-6Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/3/35/Make-a-French-Bench-from-Two-Chairs-Step-6Bullet1.jpg/aid3045272-v4-728px-Make-a-French-Bench-from-Two-Chairs-Step-6Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"485","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Grab a saw and cut some long pieces of wood. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/e9/Make-a-French-Bench-from-Two-Chairs-Step-6Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-French-Bench-from-Two-Chairs-Step-6Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/e/e9/Make-a-French-Bench-from-Two-Chairs-Step-6Bullet2.jpg/aid3045272-v4-728px-Make-a-French-Bench-from-Two-Chairs-Step-6Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"485","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Add some wood to reinforce the sides if desired so the bench will be stable. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/ef/Make-a-French-Bench-from-Two-Chairs-Step-6Bullet3.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-French-Bench-from-Two-Chairs-Step-6Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/e/ef/Make-a-French-Bench-from-Two-Chairs-Step-6Bullet3.jpg/aid3045272-v4-728px-Make-a-French-Bench-from-Two-Chairs-Step-6Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"485","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Drill two holes on the back of the chairs (where the seat used to be attached){"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/0e/Make-a-French-Bench-from-Two-Chairs-Step-6Bullet4.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-French-Bench-from-Two-Chairs-Step-6Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/0/0e/Make-a-French-Bench-from-Two-Chairs-Step-6Bullet4.jpg/aid3045272-v4-728px-Make-a-French-Bench-from-Two-Chairs-Step-6Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"485","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Screw the smaller pieces to the back of the chairs (situated where the chair seat would have been) and then attach to the longer pieces of plywood. Make sure screws are attached evenly for added support. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c3/Make-a-French-Bench-from-Two-Chairs-Step-6Bullet5.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-French-Bench-from-Two-Chairs-Step-6Bullet5.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/c/c3/Make-a-French-Bench-from-Two-Chairs-Step-6Bullet5.jpg/aid3045272-v4-728px-Make-a-French-Bench-from-Two-Chairs-Step-6Bullet5.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"485","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Apply primer first. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/80/Make-a-French-Bench-from-Two-Chairs-Step-10Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-French-Bench-from-Two-Chairs-Step-10Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/8/80/Make-a-French-Bench-from-Two-Chairs-Step-10Bullet1.jpg/aid3045272-v4-728px-Make-a-French-Bench-from-Two-Chairs-Step-10Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"485","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Consider covering it with up to three coats and possibly add a gloss topcoat to protect it from wear and tear. You may also want to add a waterproofing coat to seal it if the bench will be sitting outside. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/96/Make-a-French-Bench-from-Two-Chairs-Step-10Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-French-Bench-from-Two-Chairs-Step-10Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/9/96/Make-a-French-Bench-from-Two-Chairs-Step-10Bullet2.jpg/aid3045272-v4-728px-Make-a-French-Bench-from-Two-Chairs-Step-10Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"485","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
